.TH "dwc2_hc_init" 9 "dwc2_hc_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dwc2_hc_init \- Prepares a host channel for transferring packets to/from a specific endpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dwc2_hc_init
.BI "(struct dwc2_hsotg *hsotg "  ","
.BI "struct dwc2_host_chan *chan "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hsotg" 12
Programming view of DWC_otg controller
.IP "chan" 12
Information needed to initialize the host channel
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The HCCHARn register is set up with the characteristics specified in chan.
Host channel interrupts that may need to be serviced while this transfer is
in progress are enabled.
